Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.27,0:00:06.56,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx95}Index's perfect memorization isn't a life-threatening condition even if her memories aren't erased in one year periods.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.04,0:00:10.36,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That means The Church lied to Stiyl and Kanzaki?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.65,0:00:19.15,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Successfully constructed the most effective weapon against the intruder.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.40,0:00:24.70,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Now initiating local weapon, "St. George's Sanctuary".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.70,0:00:26.68,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Proceeding to destroy intruder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:17.57,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I forgot to ask one thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.13,0:02:20.03,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...the reason why a non-esper like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.46,0:02:22.66,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...can't use magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.55,0:02:53.44,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.65,0:02:55.86,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,Why can she... use magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.97,0:02:58.32,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.07,0:03:04.03,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That Index can't use magic... was simply The Church's lie!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.88,0:03:07.16,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.80,0:03:11.71,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,And the fact Index would die if her memories weren't erased in one year periods is a big fat lie, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.66,0:03:16.69,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Her brain is just filled with The Church's magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:22.48,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Erase all that and there wouldn't be any need to erase her memories anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.86,0:03:24.46,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.03,0:03:26.59,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.59,0:03:29.56,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...those people that forced her to take on the harsh role of being the index of prohibited books...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.03,0:03:34.69,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...would kindly tell lower level members like you the entire truth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:39.18,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,If not, then ask Index personally!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.32,0:03:44.91,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,St. George's Sanctuary does not seem to be effective against the intruder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:49.70,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Switching to other spells and proceeding with the destruction of the intruder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.18,0:04:02.22,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Fortis931!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.84,0:04:17.35,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need a vague possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:22.03,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,If her memories are erased, then at least she'll still have her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.73,0:04:25.07,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill anyone for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.58,0:04:27.18,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I'll destroy whatever is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.18,0:04:28.49,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,That was my choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.94,0:04:31.16,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,One that I made long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.98,0:04:35.73,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,"At least", huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:39.44,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's wrong; screw that kind of pathetic thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.92,0:04:42.76,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Just answer me one thing, magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.35,0:04:45.72,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want to save Index?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.30,0:04:48.97,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You guys have been waiting for this, haven't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.36,0:04:51.96,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,A method where you don't need to take away Index's memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.96,0:04:54.14,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,A method where you don't need to be Index's enemies...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.84,0:04:58.15,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,A method where everyone is smiling and that everyone wants...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.15,0:05:00.45,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...that leads to the best happy ending!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.97,0:05:04.22,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You've been waiting all your lives for this, haven't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.22,0:05:05.76,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,For this development?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.19,0:05:09.24,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,What have you guys been clenching your teeth all this time for?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.66,0:05:15.18,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you swear you'd save this one girl with your own hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.11,0:05:18.51,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You'd like to be the main characters of the story, too, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.97,0:05:21.65,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Quit being content staying a side character!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.09,0:05:26.55,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you want to put your lives on the line and protect this one girl?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.45,0:05:29.26,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it's not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.58,0:05:31.22,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't even begun!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.46,0:05:35.18,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Quit getting depressed in this kinda long prologue!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.52,0:05:37.46,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You can reach her if you stretch your hand out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.40,0:05:41.15,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get this thing started already, magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.13,0:05:50.03,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,Salvare000!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.78,0:06:11.51,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,What's... this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:14.05,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,This is... Dragon's Breath!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.05,0:06:17.36,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,It's akin to St. George's dragon's attack according to legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.81,0:06:21.50,Default,Kaori,0000,0000,0000,,If you even come in contact with one feather, you'll be doomed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.06,0:06:29.59,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Innocentius!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.41,0:06:36.12,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Go, esper!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.61,0:06:42.38,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.82,0:06:44.90,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Chapter 6, Verse 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.44,0:06:47.26,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed new enemy soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.69,0:06:49.49,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Changing battle logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.17,0:06:52.22,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Commencing search trace of the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.43,0:06:54.35,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.35,0:06:59.81,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Prioritizing the destruction of the most problematic enemy, Kamijyo Touma.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.07,0:07:14.10,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.45,0:07:17.10,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Chapter 22, Verse 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.78,0:07:20.54,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Succeeded in reverse engineering of flame spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.77,0:07:25.21,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed to be a distorted interpretation of Christian doctrines, described by runes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.50,0:07:29.17,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Constructing an anti-Christian weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:36.26,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Moving St. George's Sanctuary to Stage 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:38.89,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Eli Eli Lama Sabachthani?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:38.89,Note,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?" (Matthew 27:45-46)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.48,0:07:41.57,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Innocentius!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.02,0:07:52.86,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.84,0:07:58.44,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,If this world really is functioning through Your system...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.27,0:08:00.54,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.07,0:08:03.42,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll destroy that illusion first!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.76,0:08:13.54,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,War... ning...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.54,0:08:18.42,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Final Chapter... Verse... 0...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:22.15,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"Necklace"... suffered fatal destruction...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.23,0:08:27.40,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Regeneration impo-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.63,0:09:34.89,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious ray of light and one surveillance satellite destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.27,0:09:41.39,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,You and two others that don't possess any ID came into this city, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.76,0:09:44.28,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,So, you guys don't have anything to do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.28,0:09:45.28,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.28,0:09:51.21,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,That letter seems to be from the other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.96,0:10:03.66,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I think that it's not for you, but for that kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.66,0:10:04.33,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.76,0:10:09.50,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"Salutations are worthless so let me skip that."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.44,0:10:13.49,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,You've really done it, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.49,0:10:15.30,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,...was what I wanted to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.30,0:10:20.12,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,...but if I really voiced out my personal emotions, even cutting down all the trees in the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.12,0:10:22.93,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,...wouldn't make enough paper for that purpose, so I'll refrain from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:28.25,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,As the least of courtesy I can show for your assistance in all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.25,0:10:31.75,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain the complete situation concerning you and her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.19,0:10:39.15,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,The English Purist Church wished to immediately take her back,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.89,0:10:43.04,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,but when we asked for an explanation for lying to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.04,0:10:45.56,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,they suddenly decided to maintain the current status quo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.16,0:10:49.31,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure it's more accurate to say they want to monitor developments.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.84,0:10:55.40,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Me, personally, I can't tolerate any second you're around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.06,0:11:02.80,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, this doesn't exactly mean we're giving her to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.94,0:11:11.36,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,We will collect information and retrieve her once we have gathered proper equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.70,0:11:15.02,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my style to kill you in your sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.45,0:11:17.98,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"...so clean your neck and wait for us."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.43,0:11:26.22,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,A rather extreme friend you have there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.68,0:11:29.72,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if he mixed in some liquid explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:44.27,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be faster if you'd go see that kid in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.68,0:11:46.26,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'd like to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.04,0:11:51.21,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it'd be rude to be shocked when you do see him,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.21,0:11:53.43,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,so let me give you a quick and dirty lesson #1.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.68,0:12:12.42,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.95,0:12:36.92,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.35,0:12:46.91,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.61,0:12:53.62,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come to the wrong room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.08,0:13:00.67,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,That's memory destruction, rather than memory loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.30,0:13:03.37,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Memory destruction?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.37,0:13:05.77,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't forget his memories,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.77,0:13:08.97,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,but rather his brain cells were physically destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.68,0:13:12.39,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he'd remember anything to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.11,0:13:14.51,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.51,0:13:17.74,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Did they open up his noggin and use a stun gun on him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.69,0:13:25.31,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.89,0:13:28.11,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.84,0:13:31.21,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be in great pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.40,0:13:35.37,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.37,0:13:36.44,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.89,0:13:39.54,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'm okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.50,0:13:42.30,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.91,0:13:45.72,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Do we know each other by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.81,0:13:49.21,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.90,0:13:53.24,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,We first met on the balcony of your student dormitory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.25,0:13:57.26,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I lived in a student dormitory?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:00.70,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.36,0:14:05.86,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,My Walking Church got destroyed by your right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.34,0:14:08.50,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,What's... a walking church?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.04,0:14:10.70,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Some kind of walking club?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.17,0:14:13.84,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.82,0:14:19.29,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,You fought against magicians for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.14,0:14:22.50,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Whose name is Touma?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.42,0:14:25.90,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma... don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.70,0:14:27.96,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Index...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:32.68,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Index... loved you, Touma...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.35,0:14:37.12,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, what's index?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.58,0:14:39.43,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it's not a person's name...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.84,0:14:42.31,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Did I have a pet dog or cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.30,0:14:55.88,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,JUST KIDDING!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.72,0:14:58.42,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You fell for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.40,0:15:08.01,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting all emotional for being called a dog or cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.01,0:15:09.72,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You must be that type.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:11.43,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You like collars?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.43,0:15:15.22,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Are you requesting me to do that kind of stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.44,0:15:17.52,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.04,0:15:23.20,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, weren't your brain cells blown away?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.20,0:15:24.73,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you forget everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:29.82,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,You sound as if it'd be better if I did forget everything, yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.25,0:15:32.02,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.49,0:15:34.89,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,According to that frog-faced doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.89,0:15:37.24,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,my brain cells got destroyed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.90,0:15:41.34,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I should've lost my memories, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.85,0:15:43.71,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,"Should've"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:45.48,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.48,0:15:48.44,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,The damage was caused by magic, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.88,0:15:50.69,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.30,0:15:53.80,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I touched my head with my right hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.80,0:15:57.93,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,...and directed Imagine Breaker towards myself and voila.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.29,0:16:00.31,Default,Index,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine... Breaker?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.79,0:16:02.15,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,The name for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.55,0:16:04.59,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the doctors called it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.59,0:16:06.94,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,In simple terms, before the damage reached the brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:10.78,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I just needed to dispel the magical damage, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.24,0:16:17.02,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,And look at you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.40,0:16:20.83,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,For all the problems you caused to others this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.83,0:16:25.21,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,you can take a good long look at yourself in the mirror, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.47,0:16:27.02,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.20,0:16:54.88,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this is a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.88,0:16:57.07,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to die... really...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.35,0:17:05.04,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,But, was that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.69,0:17:10.84,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't remember anything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.43,0:17:16.29,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,I told you word for word what I heard from those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.84,0:17:25.32,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I... just didn't want that girl to cry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.05,0:17:28.38,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's what crossed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.74,0:17:35.86,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what this emotion is,\Nand I'm sure I won't ever remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.46,0:17:41.26,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,But that's what crossed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.87,0:17:45.54,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps, I still remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:50.92,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Your memories are dead, along with your brain cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.77,0:17:54.88,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,No information remains in your brain, or should, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.75,0:18:00.13,Default,doctor,0000,0000,0000,,Then, where are your memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.96,0:18:04.24,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.94,0:18:10.44,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,My heart, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.41,0:18:28.72,Default,broadcast,0000,0000,0000,,Two weeks have passed since the interruption of communication with artificial satellite, Orihime-01,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.72,0:18:32.17,Default,broadcast,0000,0000,0000,,yet there is still no indication as to when communications will be restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.17,0:18:37.28,Default,broadcast,0000,0000,0000,,It has been decided the board will have immediate discussions concerning future goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.49,0:18:53.30,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Stiyl Magnus.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.01,0:19:00.93,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Every single person that comes here looks at how I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.93,0:19:02.81,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,...and reacts in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.80,0:19:09.65,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,"There shouldn't be a need to let a human do something machines do," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.55,0:19:11.43,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.88,0:19:13.83,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,General Superintendent Aleister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.44,0:19:20.06,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you already know the reason for being recalled from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.99,0:19:22.72,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,The situation has become complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.35,0:19:25.51,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,"Deep Blood", correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.58,0:19:28.89,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Its existence is uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.89,0:19:34.73,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,A girl possessing the power to kill "a certain organism", whose existence is not even certain, is being imprisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.47,0:19:42.17,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,What has complicated matters is that you magicians,\Nwho shouldn't be within this city, have taken part in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.64,0:19:43.89,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Magicians?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.85,0:19:48.74,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,It is rather easy to terminate a magician or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.90,0:19:52.25,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,That is not the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.65,0:19:54.49,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,The issue is that we, the science side,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.49,0:19:57.71,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,will end up defeating the magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.18,0:20:05.41,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Because the science side and the magic side both hold their own exclusive technologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.41,0:20:07.69,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,the balance of the world exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.90,0:20:14.81,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,It is rather obvious what would happen if Academy City, which governs all espers,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.68,0:20:17.85,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,insists that it has defeated magicians, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.16,0:20:20.19,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.23,0:20:26.79,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,If I, a magician, take out someone from the magic side,\Nno one would have a problem with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.79,0:20:28.13,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.31,0:20:36.17,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,And I also possess a natural enemy of magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.93,0:20:39.05,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine Breaker...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.84,0:20:44.72,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,But is it not dangerous to be using an esper?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.07,0:20:46.46,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,There are no problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.79,0:20:48.47,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,He is Level 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.47,0:20:49.90,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,A "powerless" person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.71,0:20:53.25,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,He does not possess any valuable information.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.77,0:20:59.36,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,There are no fears that our information would be leaked by him accompanying you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.79,0:21:03.57,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling me... to partner up with that kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.29,0:21:07.07,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,He knows your technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.07,0:21:09.53,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,but has no intelligence to re-create it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.22,0:21:13.41,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, you don't have to worry\Nthat your information might be leaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.09,0:21:16.34,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Understood...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.04,0:21:22.84,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.76,0:21:28.19,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,...does "Deep Blood" really exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.09,0:21:32.43,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,If it really does exist, then that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.17,0:21:38.19,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,...that the "certain organism" that it needs to kill also exists...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.22,0:21:40.40,Default,Stiyl,0000,0000,0000,,Vampires...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.64,0:21:47.44,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,I believe occult affairs are not\Nour area of expertise, but yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.38,0:21:49.44,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,Well then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.13,0:21:54.95,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,If Deep Blood proves the existence of vampires,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.43,0:22:00.36,Default,Aleister,0000,0000,0000,,then whose existence will the Imagine Breaker prove?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.67,0:23:38.27,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,The Alchemist, Aureolus Izzard's target, the Deep Blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.27,0:23:39.98,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,That girl being imprisoned in Misawa cram school is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.62,0:23:42.90,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, magician?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.18,0:23:44.85,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Science Worship".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.35,0:23:47.23,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,When science and magic cross paths,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.23,0:23:48.42,Default,Touma,0000,0000,0000,,this epic will begin!
